{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/go-swagger/go-swagger/issues/707","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/go-swagger/go-swagger","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/go-swagger/go-swagger/issues/707/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/go-swagger/go-swagger/issues/707/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/go-swagger/go-swagger/issues/707/events","html_url":"https://github.com/go-swagger/go-swagger/issues/707","id":184381884,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxODQzODE4ODQ=","number":707,"title":"can't distinguish between an empty array and null array for non-required array fields","user":{"login":"rgarcia","id":72655,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcyNjU1","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/72655?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rgarcia","html_url":"https://github.com/rgarcia","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rgarcia/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rgarcia/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rgarcia/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rgarcia/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rgarcia/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rgarcia/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rgarcia/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rgarcia/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rgarcia/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":148436506,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxNDg0MzY1MDY=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/go-swagger/go-swagger/labels/enhancement","name":"enhancement","color":"84b6eb","default":true,"description":null}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2016-10-21T01:52:39Z","updated_at":"2016-10-24T22:00:50Z","closed_at":"2016-10-24T22:00:50Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Problem statement\n\nFor this spec that contains a model with a non-required array field:\n\n``` yaml\nswagger: '2.0'\ninfo:\n  title: swagger spec with a model with a non-required array field\n  version: 0.1.0\ndefinitions:\n  Foo:\n    type: object\n    properties:\n      arrayThing:\n        type: array\n        items:\n          type: string\n```\n\nThe generated model looks like this:\n\n``` go\n// Foo foo\n// swagger:model Foo\ntype Foo struct {\n\n    // array thing\n    ArrayThing []string `json:\"arrayThing,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe use of `omitempty` here is problematic when clients and servers would like to differentiate between the case when the array is omitted and when the array is empty.\n\nWhen a client goes to marshal the omitted case, e.g. `Foo{}`, the result (as expected) is an empty JSON object, `{}`.\n\nHowever, when a client goes to marshal the empty array case, e.g. `Foo{ArrayThing:[]string{}}`, the result is _also an empty JSON object_ (`encoding/json` treats length zero slices as empty).\n\nYou can see this behavior here: https://play.golang.org/p/KTH36qo8mu\n\nThis means the server cannot distinguish between these two cases when processing `Foo`s sent by clients.\n\nI think this is easily fixable by dropping `omitempty` on non-required array fields. This achieves the desired result: https://play.golang.org/p/nRYCj_w9-j\n","closed_by":{"login":"casualjim","id":456109,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ1NjEwOQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/456109?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/casualjim","html_url":"https://github.com/casualjim","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/casualjim/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/casualjim/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"ht